ledger (3.0.0~20100615-0mbudde1) lucid; urgency=low

  * Beta release 1.
  * debian/rules:
    * Don't build and install PDF and HTML documentation.
      PDF documentation is installed by make.
    * Don't copy config.{guess,sub} from /usr/share/misc.
  * debian/control:
    * Add missing dependencies.
    * Update maintainer.
  * Add binary package ledger-el
    * Add section in debian/control
    * Fix installation path of ledger.el in debian/rules.
    * Move emacsen-startup to ledger-el.emacsen-startup.
    * Add ledger-el.dirs.
  * Remove debian-supplied manpage; added upstream.
  * Remove debian/dirs.
  * Switch to dpkg-source 3.0 (quilt) format
  * Add dependency on quilt.
  * Use an install file instead of copying ledger.el by hand in
    debian/rules.
  * Remove build dependency libexpat.
  * Enable python support.

 -- Michael Budde <mbudde@gmail.com>  Fri, 28 May 2010 11:45:39 +0200

ledger (2.6.2-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * CONSTipate gnucash.cc, textual.cc, and option.cc, so it builds with GCC
    4.4.  Thanks to Stefan Ebner for the patch.  Closes: #547303.
  * Install a man page (this will become redundant once 3.0 comes out, but
    until then...).  Thanks to Carl Worth for the manpage.  Closes: #540409.
  * Install emacs mode for ledger (ledger.el); untested, as I have no emacs
    fu, but here's hoping... Thanks to Kevin Ryde for the patch.
    Closes: #554040.
  * Bumped standards version; no changes required.

